  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Socio-Economic Reintegration of Returnees and Other Vulnerable Households in Migration Affected Areas Severely Impacted By COVID-19 Pandemic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to support the sustainable reintegration of returnees who continue to come back to Lesotho through official borders and informal crossings (nicknamed &#x201C;community crossings&#x2019;&#x2019;) from South Africa since March 2020 when South Africa implemented the COVID-19 lockdown and border closure. In line with its long-standing mandate and multi-sectoral expertise, IOM advocates for the adoption of sustainability-oriented reintegration policies that respond to the economic, social and psychosocial needs of returning migrants while also benefiting communities of origin and addressing structural challenges to reintegration.</narrative>
  </description>
